♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:15.787 --> 02:17.311
-[SCREECHING]

03:37.652 --> 03:39.131
-[ENGINES ROARING]

04:13.340 --> 04:14.906
-[SIREN BLARING]

04:19.346 --> 04:20.911
-IF THEY CATCH ME,
I'M HISTORY.

04:21.043 --> 04:22.610
-THIS IS ONE RACE
YOU'D BETTER WIN.

05:12.747 --> 05:15.837
-THAT'S IT! THAT'S IT!
THE FINAL STRAW!

05:15.967 --> 05:17.491
-AH, WHAT THE HELL,
EVEL KNIEVEL.

05:17.621 --> 05:19.101
WE'LL GET 'EM
NEXT TIME.

05:19.231 --> 05:20.885
-THEY'LL HAVE HELL TO PAY
WHEN I CATCH 'EM.

05:21.016 --> 05:22.409
OH, I'LL BUST 'EM BOTH

05:22.539 --> 05:24.498
FOR EVADING ARREST,
AGGRAVATED ASSAULT--

05:24.628 --> 05:26.064
-AGGRAVATING
A POLICE OFFICER.

05:27.109 --> 05:30.634
-YOU NEED TO GET MUD FLAPS
ON THOSE REAR TIRES.

05:30.765 --> 05:33.768
-IS IT MY FAULT THEY MAKE YOU
RIDE A SCOOTER ON THE BEACH?

05:33.898 --> 05:35.335
FRANKLY, I THINK
IT'S EMBARRASSING.

05:35.465 --> 05:36.771
-DO YOU THINK I LIKE
WORKING ON THE BEACH?

05:36.901 --> 05:38.903
I HATE THE BEACH! I'VE
ALWAYS HATED THE BEACH!

05:39.034 --> 05:40.775
THAT'S WHY HE
SENT ME HERE.

05:40.905 --> 05:42.124
-IT'S PRETTY ROTTEN
OF YOUR CAPTAIN

05:42.254 --> 05:44.387
TO BUST YOU
FROM THE GLAMOR

05:44.518 --> 05:46.520
OF THE INNER CITY TO
THE SQUALOR OF THE BEACH.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.478
-ALL I HAD TO DO WAS APOLOGIZE
FOR BREAKING HIS NOSE,

05:48.609 --> 05:50.654
BUT NO, I GOT TO TELL HIM
I ENJOYED IT.

05:50.785 --> 05:52.352
-SOME PEOPLE JUST DON'T
APPRECIATE HONESTY.

05:52.482 --> 05:54.528
-MITCH... IT'S TIME.

05:54.658 --> 05:57.182
IT IS DEFINITELY TIME
I SWALLOWED MY PRIDE.

05:57.313 --> 05:58.836
-UH-HUH.
-ALL I GOT TO DO

05:58.967 --> 06:00.925
IS WALK INTO HIS OFFICE,
SAY, "CAPTAIN TUNNEY,

06:01.056 --> 06:04.494
I REALIZE I WAS WRONG FOR
GETTING SO ANGRY THAT I--"

06:04.625 --> 06:06.801
-"RAMMED MY FIST
INTO YOUR NOSE."

06:06.931 --> 06:11.327
"...THAT I LASHED OUT
MERELY BECAUSE YOU TOOK CREDIT

06:11.458 --> 06:13.982
"FOR A BUST I HAD WORKED ON
FOR SIX MONTHS

06:14.112 --> 06:17.115
AND THEN SET ME UP
TO TAKE THE FALL FOR A BUST
YOU MESSED UP!"

06:17.246 --> 06:19.596
-SOUNDS LIKE YOU HAVEN'T
TOTALLY COME TO TERMS
WITH THIS YET.

06:19.727 --> 06:21.946
-NO. I'M CALM.

06:22.077 --> 06:23.078
IT'S ALL IN THE PAST.

06:23.208 --> 06:25.689
TIME TO FORGIVE AND FORGET.

06:26.429 --> 06:28.475
MITCH, MY FRIEND,

06:28.605 --> 06:31.826
NEXT TIME YOU'RE DOWNTOWN,
YOU STOP IN, AND I'LL BUY
YOU LUNCH.

06:31.956 --> 06:34.437
-YOU WON'T LAST A WEEK
IN AN OLD, STUFFY OFFICE.

06:35.133 --> 06:36.004
-BET.

06:36.134 --> 06:39.007
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

06:41.226 --> 06:43.359
AH, NICE WORKING
WITH YOU.

06:43.490 --> 06:45.056
[CONTINUES LAUGHING]

06:46.971 --> 06:48.799
-HE'S BEEN OUT
IN THE SUN TOO LONG.

06:51.236 --> 06:52.629
-[INDISTINCT]

06:54.022 --> 06:56.372
-COME ON, C.J.,
ORIENTATION WILL
BE MY FIRST DAY

06:56.503 --> 06:57.982
AT MALIBU BEACH HIGH.

06:58.113 --> 07:00.115
FIRST IMPRESSIONS
ARE EVERYTHING.

07:01.508 --> 07:03.205
-DON'T MOST OF THE KIDS
ALREADY KNOW YOU FROM THE BEACH?

07:03.335 --> 07:05.425
-YEAH, IN MY
LIFEGUARD UNIFORM.

07:05.555 --> 07:07.078
COME ON, THIS IS DIFFERENT,
IT'S SCHOOL.

07:07.209 --> 07:08.515
YOU'RE JUDGED ON TWO
THINGS:

07:08.645 --> 07:10.865
YOUR CLOTHES
AND THE GUY YOU'RE DATING.

07:10.995 --> 07:13.345
-WELL, THE GUY YOU'RE DATING
IS SLADE, THE SURF GOD.
I MEAN, HE'S GORGEOUS.

07:13.476 --> 07:15.347
THE GIRLS ARE GOING TO GO CRAZY
WHEN THEY SEE YOU WITH HIM.

07:15.478 --> 07:17.045
-YEAH, I KNOW.

07:17.175 --> 07:19.526
[SIGHS] STILL, I JUST
THINK I NEED A NEW OUTFIT.

07:19.656 --> 07:21.441
WON'T YOU HELP ME
PICK IT OUT. PLEASE?

07:21.571 --> 07:23.007
-OKAY.

07:23.138 --> 07:25.314
I KNOW THIS GREAT BOUTIQUE
ON THE PIER.

07:25.445 --> 07:27.795
IT'S TOTALLY OUTRAGEOUS,
THE STUFF WILL LOOK GREAT ON
YOU. COME ON, LET'S GO.

07:27.925 --> 07:29.274
-HOW OUTRAGEOUS?

07:29.405 --> 07:30.667
C.J.!

07:30.798 --> 07:32.539
-MATT'S ON THE PHONE.

07:32.669 --> 07:33.061
-TOWERS 16 AND 18.
YEAH, I'LL BE RIGHT
THERE, THANKS.

07:37.718 --> 07:39.284
YEAH, MATT, WHAT'S UP?

07:39.415 --> 07:41.025
-SORRY, MITCH. I REALLY
WANTED TO WORK THIS WEEKEND,

07:41.156 --> 07:43.854
BUT WITH SCHOOL
STARTING MONDAY...

07:43.985 --> 07:45.682
AND MY PARENTS
ARE OUT OF TOWN...

07:45.813 --> 07:47.075
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
IT'S GOING TO BE A SLOW
WEEKEND.

07:47.205 --> 07:48.685
WE'VE GOT PLENTY OF GUARDS.
-THANKS.

07:48.816 --> 07:50.034
-MATT, WE WERE CHASING
A COUPLE KIDS

07:50.165 --> 07:51.819
ON DUNE BUGGIES RACING ILLEGALLY

07:51.949 --> 07:53.647
ON CORTEZ BEACH
THIS MORNING.

07:53.777 --> 07:55.518
WE THINK THE DRIVERS
GO TO MALIBU BEACH HIGH.

07:55.649 --> 07:57.041
ASK AROUND, SEE WHAT YOU
CAN FIND OUT, WILL YOU?

07:57.172 --> 07:58.303
-YEAH, SURE,
I'LL ASK AROUND.

07:58.434 --> 07:59.391
-APPRECIATE IT.

07:59.522 --> 08:01.176
-I'LL SEE YOU IN THE WATER.

08:03.178 --> 08:04.440
HE DOESN'T KNOW IT WAS US.

08:04.571 --> 08:05.920
-DOES THAT MEAN
THE PARTY'S STILL ON?

08:06.660 --> 08:08.052
YEAH!

09:17.948 --> 09:19.254
-THIS IS A PRIVATE BEACH.

09:19.384 --> 09:20.908
-I'M NOT ON THE BEACH.

09:21.038 --> 09:22.953
-YOU WERE ON THE WAVES.

09:23.084 --> 09:24.302
MY FAMILY OWNS
EVERYTHING

09:24.433 --> 09:26.217
FROM THAT RANCH ON THE BLUFF

09:26.348 --> 09:28.437
TO THIS BEACH
WHERE THESE WAVES BREAK.

09:30.657 --> 09:32.006
-I'M IMPRESSED.

09:33.050 --> 09:34.486
-TELL ME SOMETHING.

09:34.617 --> 09:37.141
WHY DID YOU TRANSFER
TO MALIBU BEACH HIGH?

09:37.272 --> 09:39.143
-WELL, I DON'T HAVE
TO DITCH SCHOOL TO SURF.

09:39.274 --> 09:40.841
I TAKE IT FIRST PERIOD.

09:40.971 --> 09:43.931
-HMM. I'VE NEVER
UNDERSTOOD SURFING.

09:44.758 --> 09:47.021
WHAT DO YOU GET
OUT OF RIDING WAVES?

09:47.151 --> 09:48.544
-WHAT DO YOU GET
OUT OF RIDING HORSES?

09:49.545 --> 09:51.808
-I LOVE THE WAY A HORSE
FEELS WHEN HE'S UNDER ME.

09:52.461 --> 09:54.942
BEING IN CONTROL OF
SOMETHING SO POWERFUL.

09:56.465 --> 09:57.901
-WELL, SUBSTITUTE
A WAVE FOR A HORSE,

09:58.032 --> 09:59.599
AND YOU'VE GOT
YOUR ANSWER.

09:59.729 --> 10:00.861
-HMM.

10:02.558 --> 10:03.603
-SEE YOU.

10:04.560 --> 10:05.909
-EVERYONE SAYS
THAT YOU'RE GOOD ENOUGH

10:06.040 --> 10:07.694
TO BE ON
THE PRO-SURFING TOUR.

10:07.824 --> 10:08.738
WHY AREN'T YOU?

10:09.739 --> 10:10.871
-WELL, IT TAKES
A LOT OF MONEY

10:11.001 --> 10:11.959
TO TRAVEL
AROUND THE WORLD.

10:12.699 --> 10:15.440
-WELL, WHAT IF YOU HAD
A SPONSOR?

10:15.571 --> 10:16.746
-WELL, I DON'T.

10:16.877 --> 10:18.530
-WELL, WHAT IF I
COULD GET YOU ONE?

10:18.661 --> 10:21.751
SOMEONE WHO WOULD PAY
FOR YOUR TRAVELS...

10:21.882 --> 10:24.928
HOTEL, AIRFARE, ENTRY FEE.

10:25.059 --> 10:27.017
-LIKE WHO?

10:27.148 --> 10:30.499
-WELL, IF YOU'RE AS
GOOD AS THEY SAY,
WE'LL HAVE OUR PICK.

10:30.630 --> 10:31.979
MY MOTHER'S A MANAGER.

10:32.109 --> 10:35.547
SHE MANAGES SINGERS,
DANCERS, WRITERS.

10:36.418 --> 10:38.333
SHE'S NEVER HANDLED
AN ATHLETE.

10:39.421 --> 10:41.031
I WANT TO.

10:41.162 --> 10:43.077
I WANT TO DO SOMETHING
MY MOTHER HAS NEVER DONE BEFORE.

10:44.731 --> 10:46.341
-WHAT'S IN IT
FOR YOU?

10:47.690 --> 10:49.605
-15 PERCENT
OF EVERYTHING YOU MAKE...

10:50.693 --> 10:52.173
PRIZE MONEY, ENDORSEMENTS,

10:52.303 --> 10:53.914
MERCHANDISING.

10:55.350 --> 10:57.613
SAY YES,
AND I CAN MAKE IT HAPPEN.

11:18.808 --> 11:22.333
♪ THE TIME IS NOW

11:22.464 --> 11:25.728
♪ CAUSE WE ARE YOUNG, SO YOUNG

11:26.816 --> 11:29.732
♪ OUR LOVE IS NEW

11:29.863 --> 11:34.389
♪ AND I BELIEVE, YOU ARE THE ONE

11:35.695 --> 11:41.091
♪ I HAVE NEVER FELT THIS WAY
♪ ABOUT ANYONE

11:41.222 --> 11:43.006
♪ [ANYONE]

11:43.137 --> 11:47.054
♪ EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU GETS MY

11:47.184 --> 11:50.927
♪ HEART ON THE RUN

11:51.058 --> 11:56.977
♪ I'M ALIVE BECAUSE YOU ALWAYS SHINE

11:57.107 --> 12:00.937
♪ JUST LIKE THE SUN I CAN'T DENY

12:01.068 --> 12:05.899
♪ AND I WON'T EVEN TRY, YOU ARE THE ONE

12:22.872 --> 12:28.182
♪ I HAVE NEVER FELT
♪ THIS WAY ABOUT ANYONE

12:28.312 --> 12:30.619
♪ [ANYONE]

12:30.750 --> 12:36.756
♪ EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU GETS
♪ MY HEART ON THE RUN

12:41.282 --> 12:43.284
-[EXCLAIMING]

12:43.980 --> 12:45.808
BEAR, MAN,
WHERE YOU BEEN ALL SUMMER?

12:45.939 --> 12:48.071
-I'VE BEEN OUT IN THE DESERT,
MAN, PURIFYING MY SOUL.

12:48.202 --> 12:50.639
HEY, MAN, YOU COULD USE A LITTLE
PURIFICATION YOURSELF, BRODY.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.120
-THE DESERT?
ALL THAT SAND AND NO BEACH?

12:53.250 --> 12:54.382
FORGET IT, MAN.

12:54.512 --> 12:55.818
BEAR, THIS IS
SUMMER QUINN.

12:55.949 --> 12:57.385
WE WORK TOGETHER.

12:57.515 --> 12:59.604
THIS IS THE LEGENDARY
BEAR SUTTER.

12:59.735 --> 13:02.477
HIS ANCESTORS WERE IN MALIBU
BEFORE MALIBU WAS MALIBU.

13:05.045 --> 13:05.959
-IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

13:07.003 --> 13:07.961
-SUMMER?

13:09.876 --> 13:11.399
YOU KNOW,
I DIDN'T FIGURE SLADE

13:11.529 --> 13:12.966
WOULD BE A TARGET
FOR COURTNEY'S TROPHY CASE.

13:13.705 --> 13:14.924
SHE'S WHAT
ALEXIS CARRINGTON

13:15.055 --> 13:16.099
MUST HAVE BEEN LIKE
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

13:16.230 --> 13:17.100
-BE RIGHT BACK.

14:22.687 --> 14:23.558
-HI, SUMMER.

14:24.646 --> 14:26.517
HEY, I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL,
MY DAD'S A MARINE.

14:26.648 --> 14:28.868
EVERY TIME HE TRANSFERRED,
I HAD TO FIND A NEW SCHOOL.

14:28.998 --> 14:31.261
-YEAH, WELL, THERE'S NO
MARINE BASE IN MALIBU.

14:31.392 --> 14:33.698
-I KNOW. THAT'S WHY I CAME
HERE, TO GET AWAY FROM HIM.

14:34.395 --> 14:36.049
EVERY TIME HE GOT DRUNK,
I BECAME THE ENEMY.

14:37.311 --> 14:38.573
I LIKE YOUR OUTFIT.
IS IT NEW?

14:39.226 --> 14:40.967
-NO, IT'S NOTHING SPECIAL.

14:41.706 --> 14:43.143
-SO WHAT CLASS
YOU GONNA TAKE?

14:43.708 --> 14:45.101
-WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT MAKE?

14:45.232 --> 14:46.886
-MAYBE WE CAN GET IN
SOME OF THE SAME ONES.

14:47.887 --> 14:50.498
-WHY DON'T YOU GO GET IN THE
SAME ONES AS COURTNEY BREMMER.

14:50.628 --> 14:52.282
THEN, YOU GUYS
CAN WALK ARM-IN-ARM

14:52.413 --> 14:54.284
FROM ONE CLASS TO THE OTHER.
-LOOK, IT'S JUST BUSINESS.

14:54.415 --> 14:55.633
SHE'S JUST TRYING TO
HELP ME GET A SPONSOR,
THAT'S ALL.

14:55.764 --> 14:57.635
-OH, RIGHT.

14:57.766 --> 14:59.376
WHY DON'T YOU GO WATCH
RERUNS OF "DYNASTY" OR
SOMETHING?

14:59.507 --> 15:01.161
-[MOUTHING] WHAT?

15:02.379 --> 15:04.338
-OKAY, LET'S LISTEN UP.

15:04.468 --> 15:05.948
HAVE YOUR ATTENTION?

15:06.079 --> 15:07.863
THANK YOU, THANK YOU,
THANK YOU, THANK YOU.

15:07.994 --> 15:11.345
HELLO. WELCOME
TO MALIBU BEACH HIGH.

15:11.475 --> 15:12.955
MY NAME IS FRANK RICHMOND.

15:13.086 --> 15:14.609
I AM YOUR PRINCIPAL.

15:14.739 --> 15:17.220
FIRST OFF, I'D LIKE TO
DISPEL SOME OF THE MALIBU HYPE.

15:17.351 --> 15:19.527
YES, WE DO HAVE SURFING CLASSES.

15:19.657 --> 15:21.790
YES, WE DO HAVE
BEACH VOLLEYBALL TEAMS,

15:21.921 --> 15:25.228
BUT WE ALSO HAVE ONE OF
THE MOST DEMANDING CURRICULA

15:25.359 --> 15:27.361
OF ANY SCHOOL
IN THIS COUNTRY.

15:34.150 --> 15:36.196
-YEAH, IT SOUNDS GREAT.
WE'LL BE THERE.

15:36.326 --> 15:37.371
-YEAH.

15:38.546 --> 15:39.895
-SEE YOU GUYS LATER.
-OKAY.

15:40.026 --> 15:41.288
-C.J.!

15:41.418 --> 15:42.506
-MATTHEW.

15:42.637 --> 15:43.377
-WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

15:44.117 --> 15:45.205
-I'M COACHING.

15:45.814 --> 15:46.771
-SINCE WHEN?

15:46.902 --> 15:48.425
-WELL, IT'S JUST TEMPORARY.

15:48.556 --> 15:50.732
THEY LOST SOME TEACHERS,
BUDGET CUTBACKS, YOU KNOW?

15:51.385 --> 15:53.648
SO A COUPLE OF US VOLUNTEERED
UNTIL THEY GET THE MONEY

15:53.778 --> 15:55.084
FROM SOME PROPERTY
THE SCHOOL SOLD OFF.

15:55.215 --> 15:56.956
-COOL. HEY,
I'M THROWING A RAGER.

15:57.086 --> 15:58.609
SATURDAY.
YOU GOT TO COME.

15:59.088 --> 16:00.829
-I'D LOVE TO,
BUT I WORK ON SATURDAY.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.831
-COME AFTER YOUR SHIFT.

16:02.962 --> 16:03.614
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
SOME VOLLEYBALL,

16:04.224 --> 16:05.442
AND WE'LL BE
UNBEATABLE.

16:05.573 --> 16:06.443
-GIVE ME MY BALL BACK.

16:07.183 --> 16:09.490
-NOT UNLESS YOU SAY
YOU'RE GOING TO COME.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.231
-GIVE ME MY BALL BACK.

16:11.361 --> 16:13.320
I'LL SEE.
-GREAT.

16:16.062 --> 16:17.106
-[CLAMORING]

16:19.021 --> 16:21.502
-BRODY:
WHAT'S GOING ON OVER THERE?
-C.J.: I DON'T KNOW.

16:33.993 --> 16:35.211
-BEAR,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:35.342 --> 16:36.952
-YOU DON'T WANT
TO STEP ON THAT, BRODY.

16:37.083 --> 16:38.780
-BEAR, WHAT'S THIS
ALL ABOUT?

16:39.476 --> 16:42.392
-IT'S ABOUT THE SCHOOL
SELLING CHUMASH LAND
TO BUILD CONDOS.

16:46.483 --> 16:48.833
-SLADE! SLADE, WE'VE GOT
TO GET DOWNTOWN BY 4:00

16:48.964 --> 16:50.357
TO MEET
WITH SID KIWITT.

16:50.487 --> 16:52.098
HE OWNS TOPANGA SWIMWEAR.

16:52.228 --> 16:53.360
HE'S INTERESTED.

17:05.849 --> 17:07.678
[INDISTINCT]

17:11.638 --> 17:13.031
-ALL RIGHT, COME ON, COME ON.

17:13.162 --> 17:14.337
BREAK IT UP,
BREAK IT UP.

17:14.468 --> 17:16.078
COME ON, MAKE WAY. COME ON.

17:16.209 --> 17:17.471
SCHOOL'S DONE FOR THE DAY.

17:17.601 --> 17:19.299
TIME TO GO HOME,
COME ON, COME ON.

17:22.084 --> 17:23.303
[SIGHS]

17:26.001 --> 17:28.830
GARY, GO TO METAL SHOP,
GET MR. EVERETT,

17:28.960 --> 17:30.701
TELL HIM TO BRING
SOME CHAIN CUTTERS.

17:30.832 --> 17:33.008
MR. SUTTER, YOU WANT
TO EXPLAIN THIS?

17:33.139 --> 17:34.966
-I TRIED TO,
BUT NONE OF YOU GUYS LISTENED.

17:35.097 --> 17:37.621
-SON, I ALREADY TOLD YOU,
THAT PROPERTY

17:37.752 --> 17:39.406
IS NOT SACRED
CHUMASH LAND.

17:39.536 --> 17:41.147
IT'S JUST ANOTHER BLUFF
OVERLOOKING THE BEACH.

17:41.277 --> 17:43.323
-IT'S THE MOST SACRED PLACE
IN MALIBU.

17:43.453 --> 17:45.977
NOW ALL YOU WANT TO DO
IS TEAR IT UP WITH BULLDOZERS

17:46.108 --> 17:47.936
AND BURY IT BENEATH BUILDINGS!

17:48.067 --> 17:50.765
-MR. RICHMOND, BEAR KNOWS A LOT
ABOUT THESE THINGS.

17:50.895 --> 17:52.375
-SO DO I. NOW, TRUST ME.

17:52.506 --> 17:54.334
IF I THOUGHT
THAT WAS SACRED CHUMASH LAND,

17:54.464 --> 17:55.987
I WOULD NEVER HAVE
APPROVED THE SALE.

17:58.381 --> 17:59.556
-MAKE WAY.

17:59.687 --> 18:00.905
-WELL, WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO CUT?

18:01.036 --> 18:02.037
-THOSE CHAINS.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

18:02.168 --> 18:03.430
-OH. YOU GOT IT.

18:03.560 --> 18:05.258
-BEAR: DON'T STEP
ON THE SUN SIGN.

18:06.824 --> 18:08.087
-IT'S JUST CHALK.
CUT HIM LOOSE.

18:11.394 --> 18:13.614
-[SCREECHING]

18:13.744 --> 18:16.660
-[STUDENTS MURMURING]

18:24.103 --> 18:26.148
-CUT THOSE
CHAINS NOW.

18:30.761 --> 18:33.460
-[CONTINUES SCREECHING]

18:42.817 --> 18:44.210
-[SIGHING]

18:59.312 --> 19:01.270
OH, THIS IS GREAT.
THIS IS JUST GREAT.

19:26.034 --> 19:27.470
-TAKING A BREATHER?

19:29.951 --> 19:31.170
-UH...

19:31.866 --> 19:35.174
THIS IS THE WOODFIELD
SECURITIES CASE.

19:35.304 --> 19:37.611
ARE YOU TELLING ME THIS
CASE WAS NEVER SOLVED?

19:37.741 --> 19:39.134
-THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE FILING IT.

19:39.265 --> 19:40.353
-I WORKED ON THIS CASE.

19:40.962 --> 19:42.485
-MAYBE THAT'S WHY
IT WAS NEVER SOLVED.

19:43.791 --> 19:45.227
-I WAS THIS CLOSE TO
BREAKING IT WHEN YOU...

19:45.358 --> 19:46.707
-WHEN I WHAT?

19:48.056 --> 19:51.364
-[SIGHS] WHEN I DISPLAYED
SUCH POOR JUDGMENT,

19:51.494 --> 19:52.887
YOU WERE COMPELLED TO DEMOTE ME.

19:53.017 --> 19:55.368
LISTEN, CAPTAIN,
THAT'S ALL IN THE PAST.

19:55.498 --> 19:57.587
LOOK, I'M TELLING YOU,
I CAN BREAK THIS CASE.

19:57.718 --> 19:59.720
LET ME TAKE A CRACK AT IT
BEFORE IT'S THROWN IN THE
CRYPT, HUH?

20:07.684 --> 20:09.120
-FILE IT.

20:10.557 --> 20:11.993
-JUST BECAUSE
YOU HAVE IT IN FOR ME,

20:12.123 --> 20:13.734
YOU'RE WILLING TO LET
A CRIME GO UNSOLVED?

20:13.864 --> 20:16.302
-YOU KNOW
THAT SINCE YOU BROKE MY NOSE,

20:16.432 --> 20:19.522
I SNORE SO LOUD, MY WIFE
HAS TO SLEEP IN ANOTHER ROOM.

20:20.610 --> 20:23.918
I'M THRILLED
YOU CAME CRAWLING BACK
ON YOUR HANDS AND KNEES.

20:24.048 --> 20:25.006
THAT'S WHERE YOU BELONG.

20:26.877 --> 20:27.791
WHAT?

20:28.662 --> 20:29.924
YOU WANT TO HIT ME?

20:30.054 --> 20:30.925
GO AHEAD.

20:31.882 --> 20:33.580
SEE WHERE IT LANDS YOU
THIS TIME.

20:34.711 --> 20:36.670
NOW, I DON'T WANT TO SEE
YOUR FACE AGAIN

20:36.800 --> 20:38.889
UNTIL EVERY ONE OF THESE
IS FILED AWAY!

20:44.852 --> 20:45.940
-[SIGHS]

21:16.710 --> 21:17.841
-JAMES!

21:36.164 --> 21:37.818
I THOUGHT
YOU WOULD BE HERE.

21:38.862 --> 21:40.429
IS THAT WHERE
YOU KEEP THE KEY?

21:40.560 --> 21:42.910
ANYONE CAN FIND IT AND
STEAL EVERYTHING YOU HAVE.

21:43.040 --> 21:43.998
-YOU DIDN'T FIND IT.

21:44.128 --> 21:46.000
-I WASN'T LOOKING FOR IT.

21:52.920 --> 21:54.574
WELL, I HOPE YOU'RE TAKING
AS GOOD CARE OF YOURSELF

21:54.704 --> 21:56.271
AS YOU DO THOSE
DAMN SURFBOARDS.

22:01.015 --> 22:02.712
-DAD, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

22:02.843 --> 22:04.714
-YOU GOING TO CHANGE
RIGHT OUT HERE?

22:04.845 --> 22:06.629
JAMES, HOW CAN YOU
LIVE LIKE THIS?

22:06.760 --> 22:08.065
-NO, THE QUESTION IS

22:08.196 --> 22:10.024
HOW COULD I LIVE
LIKE I DID BEFORE THIS?

22:17.031 --> 22:18.902
-I'M NOT UP HERE VISITING.

22:19.033 --> 22:21.165
I'M RETIRING FROM THE CORPS
NEXT MONTH.

22:21.905 --> 22:23.385
I'LL FINALLY BE A CIVILIAN.

22:24.473 --> 22:26.345
WHATEVER THE HELL THAT MEANS.

22:27.302 --> 22:30.044
A MARINE BUDDY OF MINE SET UP
A JOB INTERVIEW FOR TODAY...

22:30.174 --> 22:32.525
SECURITY GUARD, KEEPING
VAGRANTS AND TOURISTS

22:32.655 --> 22:33.482
OUT OF MALIBU COLONY,

22:34.483 --> 22:36.572
YOU KNOW, AT THE GATE.

22:38.182 --> 22:39.358
-YOU CAN'T TAKE THAT JOB.

22:39.488 --> 22:41.403
-WHY?

22:41.534 --> 22:42.926
BECAUSE YOU DECIDED YOU
DON'T WANT YOUR FAMILY
ANYWHERE NEAR YOU,

22:43.057 --> 22:44.928
I SHOULD WALK AWAY
FROM AN OPPORTUNITY?

22:45.059 --> 22:46.756
-WHAT FAMILY?
YOU DROVE MOM AWAY.

22:46.887 --> 22:49.150
THE ONLY FAMILY YOU EVER CARED
ABOUT WERE YOUR MARINE BUDDIES.

22:50.543 --> 22:51.979
-I'M STILL YOUR FATHER.

22:53.459 --> 22:55.112
-LOOK, I'M GOING PRO SOON.

22:55.243 --> 22:56.897
WHEN I MAKE ENOUGH MONEY,
I'M OUT OF HERE.

22:57.027 --> 22:58.725
MAYBE I'LL GO TO
HAWAII OR SOMEWHERE.
I DON'T KNOW.

22:58.855 --> 23:00.248
I DON'T CARE,
JUST TAKE THE JOB.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.381
-OH, THAT'S YOUR GOAL,
TO BE A SURF BUM?

23:02.511 --> 23:04.774
-BUMS DON'T MAKE MONEY
ENDORSING PRODUCTS.

23:07.255 --> 23:09.126
-YOU THINK YOU CAN EARN
A LIVING WITH THIS? HUH?

23:09.257 --> 23:11.172
YOU THINK PEOPLE
ARE GONNA PAY TWO CENTS
TO EMULATE YOU, DO YOU?

23:11.302 --> 23:13.609
HUH? WHAT? YOU GOING
TO DROP OUT OF SCHOOL?

23:13.740 --> 23:16.438
HUH? ANSWER ME,
YES OR NO?

23:16.569 --> 23:18.614
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
YOU AFRAID?

23:18.745 --> 23:20.964
YOU WANT TO GRAB THIS
AND PADDLE AWAY, DON'T YOU?

23:21.095 --> 23:22.792
YOU THINK THIS CAN GIVE YOU
SOMETHING I COULDN'T?

23:22.923 --> 23:24.185
-YES.

23:29.408 --> 23:31.235
-THAT'S NOT GOING
TO GET YOU ANYTHING.

23:31.366 --> 23:33.194
YOU DROP OUT OF SCHOOL
TO SURF,

23:33.977 --> 23:35.849
I'LL BREAK YOU IN HALF
NEXT TIME.

23:47.121 --> 23:49.210
-MY GRANDFATHER BROUGHT ME
TO THIS SACRED SPOT

23:49.340 --> 23:50.472
WHEN I WAS LITTLE.

23:51.734 --> 23:54.345
WE FOUND SHELL-BEAD MONEY
THAT MY ANCESTORS USED

23:54.476 --> 23:57.131
500 YEARS AGO DURING
THE HUTASH CEREMONY

23:57.784 --> 23:59.089
HONORING MOTHER EARTH.

23:59.655 --> 24:00.961
-WOW, YOU KNOW,
I NEVER REALLY THOUGHT

24:01.091 --> 24:02.876
ABOUT INDIANS BEING
IN MALIBU.

24:03.006 --> 24:05.705
-YEAH. BUT IT WASN'T MALIBU.

24:05.835 --> 24:08.316
IT WAS CALLED HUMALIWO.

24:08.447 --> 24:10.449
IT MEANS,
THE SURF SOUNDS LOUDLY.

24:10.579 --> 24:11.972
-THAT'S REALLY BEAUTIFUL.

24:12.102 --> 24:13.495
-THAT IS BEAUTIFUL.

24:13.626 --> 24:16.585
-IT WAS, BUT LAST YEAR,
CONSTRUCTION WORKERS

24:16.716 --> 24:18.457
DESTROYED THE SITE
OF A SUN TEMPLE

24:18.587 --> 24:20.720
TO BUILD A SENATOR'S
BEACH HOUSE.

24:20.850 --> 24:21.982
COME ON!

24:22.765 --> 24:25.768
SOON, EVERY PART
OF MY HERITAGE MAY BE GONE.

24:25.899 --> 24:27.291
-MR. RICHMOND SAID,

24:27.422 --> 24:28.771
IF WE CAN PROVE THAT
THIS LAND IS SACRED,

24:28.902 --> 24:30.817
HE MIGHT NOT GO THROUGH
WITH THE SALE.

24:30.947 --> 24:33.602
-YEAH, AND YOU SAID YOU FOUND
SOME ARTIFACTS, RIGHT?

24:33.733 --> 24:38.172
-YEAH, BUT NOW WE'D HAVE TO
DIG TO FIND IF ANY ARE LEFT.

24:38.302 --> 24:39.739
THAT WOULD DESECRATE THE LAND.

24:39.869 --> 24:42.481
-GUYS, THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMETHING WE COULD DO.

24:44.395 --> 24:46.310
-IF I CAN GET MR. RICHMOND
UP THERE TOMORROW

24:46.441 --> 24:48.574
ON THE TRADITIONAL DAY
OF THE HUTASH CEREMONY,

24:49.488 --> 24:50.532
I CAN PROVE IT TO HIM.

24:51.359 --> 24:52.621
-HOW CAN YOU PROVE IT?

24:52.752 --> 24:55.711
-THE WAY
MY GRANDFATHER TAUGHT ME.

24:58.148 --> 24:59.759
HE'LL NEVER COME.

25:00.629 --> 25:02.413
-I'LL GET HIM THERE FIRST
THING IN THE MORNING.

25:03.937 --> 25:05.460
-WHAT ABOUT YOUR BEACH PARTY?

25:05.591 --> 25:07.549
-AH, THEY CAN START
WITHOUT ME.

25:12.989 --> 25:14.382
-[SIGHS]

25:15.862 --> 25:17.864
OH. OH.

25:20.475 --> 25:22.085
YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

25:22.956 --> 25:24.087
OH...

25:24.218 --> 25:25.262
-HEY, GARNER,
YOU IN HERE?

25:28.875 --> 25:30.267
THEY SAID I'D FIND YOU
IN HERE.

25:31.051 --> 25:32.618
-HEY, MITCH,
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

25:32.748 --> 25:33.706
WELCOME TO THE CRYPT.

25:33.836 --> 25:35.185
-THANK YOU.

25:35.316 --> 25:36.970
-YOU SEE THIS FILE CABINET HERE?
-MMM-HMM.

25:37.100 --> 25:39.973
-EVERY UNSOLVED CASE
FOR THE PAST 20 YEARS.

25:41.235 --> 25:43.280
AND THEY WANT ME
TO REMOVE THE "UN"

25:43.411 --> 25:44.978
FROM AS MANY AS I CAN.

25:45.108 --> 25:46.980
-WELL, I'M SURE THIS
WITE-OUT WILL DO THE TRICK.

25:47.110 --> 25:49.025
COME ON, LET'S GET OUT OF
HERE AND GET SOME LUNCH.

25:49.722 --> 25:51.941
-I CAN'T. I GOT TO GO
THROUGH THESE CASES,

25:52.072 --> 25:54.553
AND THEY KEEP
BRINGING ME MORE.

25:54.683 --> 25:56.903
-GARNER, THIS IS WHAT
I WARNED YOU ABOUT.

25:57.033 --> 25:57.904
-WHAT?

25:58.034 --> 25:59.993
-HOT, WINDOWLESS ROOM,

26:00.123 --> 26:03.344
NO SUN, NO AIR,
NO POOL, NO PETS.

26:03.474 --> 26:07.000
NO LUNCH.
-NO SAND, NO SALT WATER.

26:07.130 --> 26:08.523
MITCH, DON'T YOU
WORRY ABOUT ME.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.525
I'LL BE OUT
OF THIS ROOM SOON ENOUGH.

26:10.656 --> 26:12.179
-WELL, I GUESS
IF YOU DO HAVE

26:12.309 --> 26:14.834
SOME INCREDIBLY CHALLENGING
CASES TO SOLVE...

26:14.964 --> 26:16.836
"RUNAWAY DOG.
SPITTING INTO THE WIND.

26:16.966 --> 26:18.359
LITTERING ON THE HIGHWAY?"

26:18.489 --> 26:20.274
I MEAN, THIS IS WHAT
MAKES YOU HAPPY, RIGHT?

26:20.404 --> 26:21.405
YOU ARE HAPPY, RIGHT?

26:21.536 --> 26:22.537
-YEAH.
-OKAY.

26:22.668 --> 26:23.799
I'LL SEE YOU.
-THANKS.

26:23.930 --> 26:25.671
-GARNER,
I MISS YOU, OKAY?

26:25.801 --> 26:27.107
I MISS YOUR LITTLE FACE,
YOU KNOW?

26:27.237 --> 26:28.499
IT'S HAPPY ONE MINUTE,
SAD THE NEXT,

26:28.630 --> 26:29.675
YOU KNOW, GRUMPY...
I LIKE THAT.

26:29.805 --> 26:30.980
-IT'S UNPREDICTABLE.
-NAH.

26:31.111 --> 26:33.113
-COME ON,
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

26:33.243 --> 26:34.854
I'LL COOK FOR YOU
ANY TIME YOU WANT AT MY HOUSE.
DINNER'S ON ME.

26:34.984 --> 26:36.986
-THAT AN INVITATION OR A THREAT?

26:37.117 --> 26:39.467
-SEE! THAT'S WHAT I MISS,
THAT SENSE OF HUMOR.

26:39.598 --> 26:41.817
COME ON.
OFFER VOID WHERE PROHIBITED.

26:41.948 --> 26:42.862
-AH.

26:45.952 --> 26:47.301
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

27:04.623 --> 27:06.189
-LISTEN.

27:06.320 --> 27:07.800
TELL ME WHAT YOU HEAR.

27:08.714 --> 27:11.151
-I HEAR THE TRAFFIC ON
PACIFIC COAST HIGHWAY,

27:11.281 --> 27:12.282
THE WIND,
THE BIRDS...

27:12.413 --> 27:13.588
-YOU KNOW WHAT I HEAR?

27:14.720 --> 27:17.200
I HEAR THE ECHO
OF THE HUTASH CEREMONY.

27:21.161 --> 27:23.772
IT TOOK PLACE RIGHT HERE
AT THE END OF EACH SUMMER.

27:23.903 --> 27:25.861
CHUMASH FAMILIES
CAME FROM AS FAR

27:25.992 --> 27:27.646
AS THE CHANNEL ISLANDS
IN THEIR PLANK CANOES

27:27.776 --> 27:29.909
TO CELEBRATE
THE ACORN HARVEST.

27:30.518 --> 27:32.694
-HOW CAN YOU BE SURE
THIS IS THE EXACT SPOT

27:32.825 --> 27:34.261
WHERE THE CEREMONY
TOOK PLACE?

27:34.391 --> 27:36.132
-THOSE HOUSES THEY'RE
BUILDING ON BEAR'S HEAD

27:36.263 --> 27:38.047
AND THOSE ON
THE BEAR'S LEG?

27:38.178 --> 27:40.789
MY GRANDFATHER BROUGHT ME HERE
TO THE BEAR'S CLAW.

27:40.920 --> 27:42.748
THIS IS WHERE HE TOLD ME
THE BEAR DANCER

27:42.878 --> 27:45.098
SHOOK HIS RATTLE AND SANG.

27:45.228 --> 27:46.621
LOOK!

27:49.058 --> 27:50.407
LISTEN!

27:50.538 --> 27:52.192
THE GROUND SHAKES!

27:52.322 --> 27:54.150
-[RATTLING]

27:54.281 --> 27:55.499
-[RUMBLING]

27:55.630 --> 27:56.936
-DO YOU HEAR THAT?

27:57.066 --> 27:57.893
-YEAH.

28:00.026 --> 28:03.377
-I AM A CREATURE
OF POWER.

28:03.507 --> 28:07.120
I WALK THE MOUNTAIN TOPS
TO EVERY CORNER OF THE WORLD.

28:07.250 --> 28:09.905
I AM A CREATURE OF POWER!

28:13.169 --> 28:17.260
MY... MY GRANDFATHER
GAVE ME MY NAME

28:17.391 --> 28:19.001
RIGHT HERE
ON THIS SPOT.

28:19.132 --> 28:21.961
-THAT DOESN'T QUALIFY
THIS AS SACRED CHUMASH LAND.

28:22.091 --> 28:23.876
AND HAVING SOMEONE HIDE

28:24.006 --> 28:27.053
AND SHAKE A RATTLE
IS A BIT HAM-HANDED,
DON'T YOU THINK?

28:27.183 --> 28:28.837
-THERE'S NOBODY HERE BUT US.

28:29.925 --> 28:31.318
TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.

28:31.448 --> 28:34.103
-I SEE THREE YOUNG,
WELL-INTENTIONED PEOPLE

28:34.234 --> 28:35.888
TRYING TO SELL ME
A BILL OF GOODS.

28:36.018 --> 28:39.369
-I SEE THE WAY THIS PLACE LOOKED
500 YEARS AGO,

28:39.500 --> 28:42.416
BEFORE THERE WAS ROADS
AND BUILDINGS.

28:42.546 --> 28:45.506
IMAGINE WHAT IT WAS LIKE
STANDING RIGHT HERE.

28:46.115 --> 28:48.074
IMAGINE WHAT IT LOOKED LIKE.

28:48.204 --> 28:49.292
IMAGINE.

28:55.603 --> 28:57.605
-BEAR, NONE OF THIS
PROVES ANYTHING.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.955
UNLESS YOU HAVE HARD EVIDENCE,

29:00.086 --> 29:02.479
I CAN'T ARGUE
TO THE SCHOOL BOARD

29:02.610 --> 29:04.394
NOT TO SELL THIS LAND.

29:04.525 --> 29:06.919
THE DISTRICT NEEDS THE
MONEY FOR OUR PROGRAMS.

29:07.049 --> 29:08.834
-YEAH, BUT YOU KNOW,
THIS IS MALIBU.

29:08.964 --> 29:11.488
THERE MUST BE SOME OTHER WAY
WE COULD RAISE MONEY.

29:11.619 --> 29:13.099
-AND THE STUDENTS
CAN CONTRIBUTE.

29:14.796 --> 29:16.319
-CAN YOU GIVE ME
ANY HARD EVIDENCE?

29:19.758 --> 29:21.063
-[SCREECHING]

29:58.927 --> 30:02.670
-[DRUMS SOUNDING]

30:39.315 --> 30:40.839
-DID YOU THREE
SET THIS UP?

30:40.969 --> 30:42.623
-YOU SAW THAT, TOO?

30:42.753 --> 30:44.364
-BEAR, MAN,
WHAT WAS THAT?

30:44.494 --> 30:45.669
-WHAT WAS WHAT?

30:45.800 --> 30:47.410
-DON'T PLAY GAMES.

30:47.541 --> 30:49.630
-BEAR, THE DEER AND THEN,
THE HUNTER...

30:49.760 --> 30:51.806
I MEAN, IT WAS JUST LIKE
THE ONES IN THE MURAL.

30:51.937 --> 30:53.025
-HE SHOT AN ARROW.

30:53.155 --> 30:54.461
-DID YOU SEE
WHERE IT LANDED?

30:55.679 --> 30:56.767
-THERE.

31:07.735 --> 31:09.737
IT LANDED
HERE SOMEPLACE.

31:20.052 --> 31:21.662
-THERE'S NO ARROW HERE.

31:29.409 --> 31:30.627
-OH, MY GOD.

31:43.379 --> 31:44.728
I DON'T KNOW WHAT JUST
HAPPENED,

31:44.859 --> 31:46.469
AND I'M NOT GOING TO TRY
AND FIGURE IT OUT,

31:46.600 --> 31:48.602
BUT IF THE COUNTY MUSEUM
SAYS THIS IS AN AUTHENTIC

31:48.732 --> 31:51.126
ANCIENT CHUMASH ARROWHEAD

31:51.257 --> 31:52.911
